r",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-01","Police: Counter-terrorism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Williams of Trafford on 24 November (HL3373), what checks are carried out by the Home Office, or by any bodies on its behalf, to ensure that police forces do not spend money allocated to counter-terrorism on activities with no connection to terrorism or serious crime.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb",,"Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb","HL3755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/649393","Home Office","false","2016-12-09","<p>Prevent is about safeguarding vulnerable people from becoming terrorists or supporting terrorism. Prevent training is kept under continued review, and feedback is provided to ensure training materials address the risk of terrorism.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2016-12-09T11:29:22.4Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/649393/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/649393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/649393/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2016-12-01","Police: Counter-terrorism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Williams of Trafford on 24 November (HL3373), what procedures exist for challenging and correcting Prevent practitioners who include participation in anti-fracking groups within their training materials.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb",,"Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb","HL3756"
